**Findings**
- Risk — [spec/v0/02-data-model.md](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/spec/v0/02-data-model.md:65), [spec/v0/schemas/proposal.schema.json](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/spec/v0/schemas/proposal.schema.json:37), [spec/v0/schemas/trial.schema.json](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/spec/v0/schemas/trial.schema.json:36): the prose still says commit SHAs use an implementation-declared length, but the schemas still hard-code 40 or 64 hex chars. If v0 intends to allow only SHA-1 and SHA-256 repos, the prose should say that explicitly; otherwise the regexes are over-constrained relative to the spec text.

The four requested re-checks look fixed on this pass. `experiment-config` now carries only host-independent core fields and leaves role binding to additional properties / Phase 2; `task.schema.json` now enforces `claim` iff `state == "claimed"`; all current timestamp fields have UTC-only `Z` patterns; and the integer/real distinction is now defined concretely enough for implementors, with runtime enforcement called out where the static schema cannot express per-experiment metric typing.

Go/no-go: **go**. I do not see a remaining merge-blocking Bug. The only issue I’d keep on the follow-up list is the SHA prose/schema drift above. I also could not rerun `check-jsonschema` locally in this sandbox because the tool is not installed and network installs are blocked, so the validation-status check here is based on direct file review rather than re-execution.
